# Frontend Environment Variables

## Development
```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
```

## Production (Render)
```
VITE_API_URL=https://cafe-backend.onrender.com/api
```

## Usage in Code
```javascript
// The environment variable is automatically injected by Vite
const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL;
```

## Important Notes

1. **VITE_ Prefix**: All frontend environment variables must start with `VITE_` to be accessible in the browser
2. **Runtime Access**: In `src/services/api.js`, the API URL is accessed via `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL`
3. **Build Time**: Environment variables are embedded at build time, so `.env.production` must be set before building
4. **Render Deployment**: The `VITE_API_URL` is automatically set via `render.yaml`

## Local Development

1. Ensure `.env.development` points to your local backend:
   ```
   VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
   ```

2. Run development server:
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

## Production Build

1. Ensure `.env.production` has the correct backend URL:
   ```
   VITE_API_URL=https://cafe-backend.onrender.com/api
   ```

2. Build:
   ```bash
   npm run build
   ```

The built files in `dist/` will have the production API URL baked in.
